doc.after: Mysore is a major tourist destination in its own right and serves as a base for other tourist attractions in the vicinity.[19] The city receives large number of tourists during the 10-day Dasara festival.[81] One of the most visited monuments in India, the Amba Vilas Palace, or Mysore Palace, is the centre of the Dasara festivities.[82] The Jaganmohana Palace, The Sand Sculpture Museum the Jayalakshmi Vilas and the Lalitha Mahal are other palaces in the city.[83] Chamundeshwari Temple, atop the Chamundi Hills, and St. Philomena's Church, Wesley's Cathedral are notable religious places in Mysore.[19]
